claim.claim-text:
1. An electric toothbrush, comprising:
a handle having an electric motor;
a head;
a neck extending between said handle and said head, said head having a first end disposed adjacent to said neck and a second end opposite to said first end, said head having a first bristle holder having a plurality of bristles disposed therein and a second bristle holder having a plurality of bristles disposed therein, wherein said first bristle holder is located at said second end of said head and said second bristle holder is located at said first end of the head and between the neck and the first bristle holder;
wherein said electric motor is operatively connected to said first and second bristle holders via a shaft that is structured to rotate thereby moving said first and second bristle holders so that the tips of the bristles of the first and second bristle holders are moved in a side-to-side direction generally transverse to both a longitudinal axis of said head and longitudinal axes of the bristles;
wherein said first bristle holder includes an upper and lower surfaces wherein the bristles extend from the upper surface, the lower surface of the first bristle holder including a plurality of cam followers that depend therefrom and operatively engage a cam on the shaft operatively connected to said electric motor, the lower surface of the first bristle holder further including a plurality of depending fingers disposed on opposite sides of the cam followers and engaged within guide slots formed on opposite sides of the head; and
static bristles disposed between the first and second bristle holders.

4. An electric toothbrush, comprising:
a handle having an electric motor;
a head;
a neck extending between said handle and said head, said head having a first end disposed adjacent to said neck and a second end opposite to said first end, said head having a first bristle holder having a plurality of bristles disposed therein and a second bristle holder having a plurality of bristles disposed therein, wherein said first bristle holder is located at said second end of said head and said second bristle holder is located between the neck and the first bristle holder;
wherein said electric motor is operatively connected to said first and second bristle holders via a shaft that is structured to rotate thereby moving said first and second bristle holders so that the tips of the bristles of the first and second bristle holders are moved in a side-to-side direction generally transverse to both a longitudinal axis of said head and longitudinal axes of the bristles;
wherein said first bristle holder includes an upper and lower surfaces wherein the bristles extend from the upper surface, the lower surface of the first bristle holder including a pair of cam followers that depend from a middle portion thereof and operatively engage a cam on the shaft operatively connected to said electric motor, the lower surface of the first bristle holder further including a pair of depending fingers disposed on opposite sides of the cam followers and engaged within guide slots formed on opposite sides of the head; and
and
static bristles disposed between the first and second bristle holders.
